    pearls: ["C-peptide is the key differentiating lab: low/undetectable = T1DM (no endogenous insulin); normal/high = T2DM (insulin resistance with preserved secretion)","Anti-GAD65 antibodies are the most sensitive autoantibody for T1DM and LADA — order in any lean adult diagnosed with T2DM who progresses rapidly to insulin requirement","DKA is primarily a T1DM complication (absolute insulin deficiency); HHS is primarily T2DM (relative insulin deficiency sufficient to prevent ketosis but not hyperglycemia)","In DKA, potassium shifts extracellularly due to acidosis — serum K+ may be normal or elevated despite total body potassium depletion; always replace K+ before or with insulin to prevent fatal hypokalemia","Metformin does NOT cause hypoglycemia as monotherapy — this is a key distinguishing feature from sulfonylureas and insulin","SGLT2 inhibitors and GLP-1 receptor agonists have proven cardiovascular and renal benefits beyond glucose lowering — prioritize these in T2DM patients with ASCVD, heart failure, or CKD","The honeymoon period in T1DM refers to a temporary phase of partial remission shortly after diagnosis when residual beta cells recover function — insulin requirements decrease but insulin should never be discontinued","HbA1c can be unreliable in conditions affecting red blood cell turnover: falsely low in hemolytic anemia, blood loss, pregnancy; falsely high in iron deficiency anemia, splenectomy"],
